ABUJA – A presidential aspirant on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Moses Ayom on Tuesday revealed what he will do when elected as President of Nigeria. Ayom, who wrote to President Muhammadu Buhari of his intention to contest the 2023 presidential poll, listed reversal of economic losses, insecurity, transformation of economy, power sector, among others as areas he would urgently look into when elected. The presidential aspirant also disclosed his readiness to “sustain the tempo of investment in the armed forces, forge alliances that ensure steady supply and availability of the most modern security equipment and promote discipline and professionalism in the rank and file of our security architecture.” FG Interventions Boosting Farmers Capacity- RIFAN Buhari Never Told Anyone That Subsidy Be Removed – Lawan Ayom, who was one of the first to declare his 2023 presidential ambition on January 1, 2022, told President Buhari in his letter that he would take urgent steps to reverse the yearly economic losses which the World Bank estimates at $26.2 billion (₦10.1 trillion). He said: “We would consolidate on your good work to break the jinx of epileptic supply in Nigeria. We are well aware of ongoing initiatives, partnerships, and projects that your administration is executing to ensure that Nigeria achieves the 24,380 MW power supply and will make their completion a key part of our agenda. “This is because we believe, as you do, that doing so would help reverse the annual economic losses attributable to inadequate power supply, which the World Bank estimates at $26.2 billion (₦10.1 trillion).” The letter tagged, ‘Indication of Interest to run for the Office of President in 2023’, reads in part: “With great humility and deference to your good self, I, Moses Chiahemba Ayom, member of the All Progressives Congress (APC) wish to formally notify you of my interest in seeking for the office of the president of the Federal Republic of Nigeria in the 2023 election under the platform of our great Party the APC.